json.text: Ro: Hey guys, it’s Ro! I’m here with my sister Mo today!
Mo: Hey everyone, we got so many requests to play another challenge game, so today
Mo: we’re gonna be playing, Will it Fondue?
Ro: Yum, yum, yum, yum, yum! And I went to twitter and I asked you guys for different
Ro: suggestions of foods we should dip, and we got so many responses.
Ro: And we had our friends pick them out, so we have no clue what we’re gonna be dipping.
Ro: These are all gonna be a mystery to us!
Ro: If you haven’t played this game before, you’re gonna take 1 of the mystery foods,
Ro: give it a dip, a taste, and decide, does it fondue. Mo: Or does it fon-dont!
Ro: Oh I’m so scared!
Mo: Alright, we’ve got both our melting pots warmed up and ready to go.
Ro: And in my pot, I’ve got light cocoa candy melts by Wilton, and my Sister’s pot,
Ro: she has some dark chocolate heated up in here, because Molly can’t have dairy!
Mo: Let’s find out what our first mystery food is!
Ro: Boo-doo-da-doo!
Mo: Taquitos!?!?
Ro: Don’t we need to use these?
Mo: I’m using my hands. Ro: No, no, you have to be fancy.
Mo: Oh… Ro: I got these fancy, OK, do you want. Mo: I want the purple one!
Ro: You want purple.
Ro: Alright, now to dip a taquito. Mo: Here we go.
Ro: Beans doesn’t go well with that…
Ro: On 3, fondue or fon-don’t, are you ready? Mo: OK ready.
Ro: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fon-don’t!
Mo: Oh yeah. Ro: Buh-luh-luh-luh-luh-luh-la!
Ro: UGH!
Ro: We’re off to a good start, now onto the next one!
Ro: Uff! Wah-wah! Mo: Carrots. Ro: Carrots!
Ro: Oh! So much fashion! You guys didn’t know this was also a fashion video.
Ro: When I dip, you dip, we dip!
Ro: Carrots don’t have that much flavor, so that’s pretty, that’s pretty good!
Mo: Mmmhmmm. Ro: Yeah. I love carrots too!
Ro: Molly you got chocolate here, let me, let me get it off for you!
Mo: Help me out girl, help me out!
Ro: If you had that hat on, it would have protected you from that. Mo: I don’t think that’s true!
Ro: It’s science Molly!
Mo: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fondue!
Mo: Alright, mystery food number 3!
Mo: CHICKEN McNUGGETS!!! Yes!
Ro: What? Mo: I mean, oh yay, oh Chicken McNuggets. Ro: Oh, it’s Chicken McNuggets.
Ro: Molly doesn’t like those at all!
Ro: OK, this is weird, just a little bit. Mo: Oh, come on! You need to dip it!
Ro: Molly oh my gosh! Mo: This is…
Ro: I’ve heard of waffles and chicken, chicken and waffles, but not chocolate…
Mo: Chicken and chocolate? Ro: Chicken and chocolate.
Mo: Maybe it’s a new thing. Ro: Maybe…
Mo: I think I did too much!
Ro: Votes are in, 1, 2, 3… Mo: Fondue! Ro: Fon-don’t!
Mo: I actually kind of liked that.
Ro: Mystery food 4, wa-da!
Mo: Oh! Ro: Oh ha-ha-ha-ha!
Mo: I’m excited for this.
Ro: Oh we use these!
Ro: These can help you pick up food, or they can also pinch your sister’s cheeks!
Mo: Don’t you! Ro: Beep-beep-beep!
Ro: Do the dip!
Ro: Mmmmm! Mo: Has a little sweet and salty thing, OK. Ro: Mmmhmm, mmhmm.
Mo: Ready to vote? 1, 2, 3.
Both: Fondue!
Mo: Yeah, that was pretty good. Ro: Yeah, that was a good one!
Mo: That was a good one!
Mo: Alright, onto mystery food number 5! Ro: Doo-doo-doo-doo!
Mo: Sushi?!?! Ro: Oh my gosh!
Ro: Oh we got a lot of different kind of rolls here.
Ro: I’m gonna go for the shrimp. Mo: Oh hopefully… Ro: Oh!
Ro: OK, well that’s just, well let me get another one here and we’ll just have a little
Ro: bit of fondue teamwork! Mo: There you go. Ro: Going on… Going on…
Ro: OK, maybe this one! Mo: Stab it, stab it! Ro: Oh yeah there we go!
Ro: I think I did too much now, because it… Oh! Oh my gosh! Mo: Oh no!
Ro: That’s just a fish dip! now…
Ro: Easy!
Mo: OK, here we go?
Mo: Mmm, mmm. Ro: Uh oh, uh oh, that’s not going down!
Ro: That’s a fondue!
Both: Fon-don’t!
Mo: Do that again! Ro: Ba-la-la-la-la! Nope! Mo: Fon-don’t do that again.
Ro: Don’t, don’t ever do that!
Ro: Please be strawberries! Please be strawberries! Mo: Bananas!
Ro:: Bananas? Mo: Yep! Ro: That’s what you want it to be?
Mo: Yep! Ro: I love bananas, OK, ready, please be strawberries!
Ro: Oh my gosh, here we go.
Mo: OK, I actually love Hotdogs, so I’m pretty curious to see how this will taste.
Ro: When Mo was little, all she would eat was cheese, bread and hot dogs, and it’s
Ro: funny because her dairy allergy developed later.
Mo: Just stop talking about my dairy allergy. Ro: I just like to embarrass her!
Ro: She also has asthma!
Mo: Oh my god!
Ro: Cheers! Mo: OK, cheers! Ro: Cheers! Mo: I feel like we’re at the campfire!
Ro: Yep! Just roasting up a little hot dog! Mo: Hot dogs on a stick... OK. Ro: Alright! All the toppings we love!
Ro: Let’s do it!
Ro: Henny! Henry is barking because he wants these.
Ro: Henny! Do you want one of this!?!?
Mo: Fon-don’t know….
Ro: Mystery food number 7!
Mo: Pickles! Ro: Oh-ha-ha-ha-ha!
Mo: I love pickles too, they’re one of my favorite foods, so, I’m excited for this!
Ro: I don’t know Molly, because whenever we go to the melting pot, they, you know,
Ro: they don’t serve pickles… I just don’t want you to be disappointed.
Mo: Maybe…. Ro: If these aren’t all you’re thinking they’ll be!
Mo: Maybe it will be better! Maybe they don’t put it on the menu because it’s too good!
Ro: Huh! Maybe it’s their secret menu!
Mo: I’m gonna ask next time. Ro: Hey, you guys got pickles?!?!
Ro: Are you ready? Mo: Mmmhmmm.
Ro: Pfft! Pfft, pfft, pfft!
Ro: What kind of a pickle is that!?!?
Ro: This is a… No that’s a dill. Mo: No that’s a sweet pickle!
Ro: No it’s sweet, a-ba-dill? Mo: That was sweet! Ro: Is this a sweet or a dill?
Ro: 1, 2, 3… Both: Fon-don’t!
Ro: Mystery food number 8, dinner is served!
Ro: Ba-dew! Mo: OK…
Ro: Alright, we’ve got little mini Slim Jims… Slap into a Slim Jim!
Ro: Doo-doo-doo!
Ro: Hmmmm… Mo: Hmmm.
Mo: OK, ready to vote? Ro: Yeah, I’m ready to vote. Mo: OK, 1, 2, 3….
Ro: Fon-don’t! Mo: Fondue.
Mo: I think you can do it, I think, I think if that’s your thing it can work.
Ro: I am hoping for marshmallows and… Candy!
Mo: Oooh! Well number 9!
Ro: Um… Mo: Fish… Sticks…
Ro: Well… Mo: Here we go. Ro: OK, don’t knock it till you try it!
Mo: Oh! Ro: It’s almost down!
Ro: Ah, oh!
Ro: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fon-don’t!
Ro: Alright, this is our last mystery food, number 10, and we haven’t had a lot of fondues…
Mo: No, mm-mmmm. Ro: A lot of fon-don’ts, are you ready?
Mo: I’m ready, as long as it’s not… Ro: She’s still hoping for pancakes!
Ro: Ah-da!
Ro: Oh my gosh! Mo: Pizza bites! Ro: They’re pizza bites!
Ro: Definitely saving the best for last, this is it! Mo: Here we go!
Ro: Mmmmmm, oh hot! Hot!
Ro: How’d you bite that? Is my cheese?
Ro: Come here, come here, oh you got chocolate lipstick.
Ro: Fon-don’t. Mo: Fon…. Don’t…
Ro: Molly what was that. Da-da, da-da-da-da!
Mo: It wasn’t, it was way better than the pickles. Ro: Yeah, oh definitely. Mo: And the sushi.
Ro: Would you serve it at restaurant Mo? Mo: Nope, OK, fon-don’t!
Ro: Alright, that is it for the Will it Fondue game, I hope you guys enjoyed it.
Ro: Mo has much more of an adventurous palate than I. Mo: I just love chocolate.
Ro: That is also a factor!
Ro: Also if you’d like to learn more about these melting pots or the candy melts that I used
Ro: today, I made 2 videos with Wilton, I’ll put a link down below, it’s on the Wilton
Ro: channel if you want to go check those out. And, please let us know what games you
Ro: would like to see Mo and I play next, write us a comment, let us know what you think.
Ro: And, if you would like to see any of our previous games, where Mo kicks my butt
Ro: in most of them, uh, we’ll have a link up here. Mo: And up here.
Ro: Mmmhmm. Alright thanks again you guys, bye-bye! Mo: Bye!
Ro: It’s raining strawberries! Hallelujah it’s raining strawberries!
Ro: Oh, this is what’s up Molly! Mo: Here we go! Ro: Molly…
Mo: Here we go, here we go! Ro: Mo, Mo, Mo, can I get one of these?
Mo: Oh wow here we go! Ro: This is my day!
Ro: 1, 2, 3… Both: Fondue!
